<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-646-430  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 646 430.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Which Computer?andP;  August 1989 p74(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Viruses. (computer viruses)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Verghis, Anoo.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A computer virus is a program that can attaches itself to acomputer's code and can alter information stored on the computer.andO;Most viral infections have been blamed on shareware, especiallygame programs and programs that come off bulletin boards.andP;  A viralinfection often is a by-product of poor systems management.andO;Computer systems should be audited and reviewed regularly.andO;Stringent access rules to computer networks should be adopted andfollowed.andP;  Large corporations are most at risk from viralinfections.andP;  Anti-viral packages can help in removing a virus froman infected system.andP;  At present is is not illegal in England towrite a virus or pass it around, but a proposed anti-hacking lawin Parliament would change that.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesPublic SoftwareAuditing of Computer SystemsAccess ControlsSecurity SoftwareLegislationProposal.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>